<br>
Ironically, the true EQ newbie of today is more clueless than we were in '99.  Yeah they know where to go to find info, the see what gear is better than what, yada yada, but they will never know the joy of being utterly surrounded by characters who are as mystified by the experience as the next fellow.<br>
<br>
And as far as, &quot;when the next game comes out, we will all be true newbies again,&quot; it's hard for me to believe, really.  Look at DAoC - everyone there who came from EQ knew just what to do when they got there.  The only real mystery was the landscapes, and EQ pulls that off with every expansion.<br>
<br>
No, I think it's safe to say that EQ is the definitive MMORPG, THE classic.  Saying there will be something coming to throw us all into a state of newbiness will now take a full revamping of the MMORPG in general.  From what I see on the horizon, it is difficult to believe this will happen any time soon, unfortunately.<br>
<br>
